          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXC8NUHihp2D32N_RBUOCjPo2-h1fqj6lHzJv_m0Mw0v7uRHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "The receptionists were attentive, explained everything well, I am a first visit user from Germany and needed urgent supervision from an MD. Also the doctor investigated me and diagnosed the tests and graduated me with a subscription to the adequate drugs I was able to attain quickly from a drug store close by. During the waiting time for the apothecary, me and my girlfriend had a short meal in a nice french bistro close by, that I think also helped healing my cold :-))) so cool that America has places that take care of people... in those not so great political times. Thank you New York. And thank you City MD Delancey!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21SdlVYcEJUbmwyYmxacFNFUXRhemhDU1hReU1WRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xfd2d709e90083bc6!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmRvUXpBTnl2blZpSEQtazhCSXQyMVE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-03-18T16:10:42+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Cindy V",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "113365178002313891800",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIc7eKLccF_bjW2mES5qmogcRunfjuuDAvVU9nomhWV-J2KbXA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I am extremely disappointed with the care my son received at CityMD. From the moment we arrived, I felt that the doctor rushed through the visit and did not take the time to properly assess his condition. My son already had a fever when we got there, yet he was not given any medication, and I was told not to give him Tylenol unless his temperature reached 100.4\u2013100.6, which felt dismissive and concerning given his symptoms. I expressed concern that his cough sounded like croup, but the doctor insisted he was fine without a thorough evaluation. Still worried, I took him to NewYork-Presbyterian Hospital, where he was properly examined and diagnosed with croup and a fever. He required a breathing treatment and was given a steroid to help open his airways. The emergency room doctor was not only concerned but visibly upset that no treatment or medication had been provided earlier, and especially alarmed by the advice I was given regarding withholding Tylenol. The difference in care was alarming. I truly feel that the provider at CityMD failed to take my concerns seriously and rushed us out without appropriate treatment or guidance. I would not return or recommend this location, and I strongly believe a review of this provider\u2019s level of care is necessary.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21aeGVVaHJWR3BDUTBNeFlsQlVNRGRTTTNKWlVtYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xfd2d709e90083bc6!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmZxeUhrVGpCQ0MxYlBUMDdSM3JZUmc%7C%7C?hl=en",
